claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for fastening tissue, comprising: 
an elongated body having a distal end and a proximal end; 
a clip holder at the elongated body distal end; 
a clip releasably secured to the clip holder; 
a suture cutter at the elongated body distal end, the suture cutter configured to perform a cutting motion when activated; 
a control element configured to be moved in a first direction and in a second direction, wherein the first direction is different from the second direction, and wherein the control element is configured to cause the clip holder to release the clip when the control element is moved in the first direction, and the control element is further configured to activate the suture cutter when the control element is moved in the second direction.

8. A device for fastening tissue, comprising: 
a generally elongated body comprising a main body and an inner body, the generally elongated body also comprising a proximal end and a distal end; 
a cutting element positioned at the generally elongated body distal end, the cutting element configured to be moved from a start position and a cutting position; 
a clip holder positioned at the generally elongated body distal end, the clip holder configured to move from a holding position to a release position; and 
a control handle positioned at the generally elongated body proximal end, the control handle configured for movement in a first direction and in a second direction, wherein movement of the control handle in the first direction moves the clip holder from the holding position to the release position, and movement of the control handle in the second direction moves the cutting device from the start position to the cutting position.

17. A device for fastening tissue, comprising: 
a generally elongated body comprising a distal end and a proximal end, and further comprising a main body and an inner body, wherein the inner body is slidably received within the main body, and an distal end of the inner body extends out from a distal opening of the main body; 
a first cutting element and a second cutting element at the distal end of the generally elongate body; 
a control element at the proximal end of the generally elongate body, the control element configured to withdraw the inner body within the main body when the control element is moved in a first direction, the control element further configured to move the cutting elements into engagement when moved in a second direction.
